      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Twilite\n## The Graph is the Product\n\nTwilite is a **graph-native workspace** where visual thinking meets AI collaboration.\n\n**The core insight:** Most graph tools treat the graph as UI state. Twilite treats it as a **durable, portable artifact** ‚Äî a file format that humans and AI agents can both read and write.\n\n| Capability | What It Means |\n|------------|---------------|\n| üåê **Web-native** | Graphs live at URLs, can be linked, embedded, shared |\n| ü§ñ **AI-first** | Agents can create, update, and reason about graphs safely |\n| ‚ö° **Executable** | Graphs can evolve from thinking ‚Üí workflows ‚Üí running code |\n\n*The editor is a means. The artifact is the thing with power.*"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-whygraphs",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Why Graphs?",
      "position": { "x": -200, "y": -180 },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 560,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Why Node Graphs?\n\n*Because anything is possible on a node graph on the web.*\n\n### Graphs Are a Universal Canvas\nA node can be **anything**: text, code, data, UI, API, AI model, video, live query. An edge can mean **anything**: flows into, depends on, triggers, contains.\n\nThere's no schema to fight. No format to escape. **You decide what nodes and edges mean.**\n\n### Graphs Are Executable\nThis isn't just visualization ‚Äî nodes can **run code**, call APIs, stream data, respond to events. The graph isn't a picture of your system. **The graph IS your system.**\n\n### The Browser Is the Runtime\nNo install. No deploy. Share a URL and it runs. The entire web platform ‚Äî fetch, canvas, websockets, workers ‚Äî is your execution environment.\n\n### Infinite Extensibility\nToday: markdown, shapes, links.\nTomorrow: live database nodes, AI inference nodes, video players, form builders, dashboards.\n\n**Plugins add new node types.** The platform grows without limits.\n\n### Composition All the Way Down\nGraphs can contain graphs. Nodes can expose handles. Build primitives, compose them into systems, share them as templates.\n\n**Graphs are the new code.**"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-oneliner",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "One-Liner",
      "position": { "x": 400, "y": -180 },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 140,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## The Pitch\n\n> **\"Figma meets ChatGPT for visual thinking.\"**\n\nDescribe what you want to an AI ‚Üí AI generates a graph ‚Üí Paste into Twilite ‚Üí Graph appears instantly.\n\nNo manual clicking and dragging. Just think, describe, and see."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-possibilities",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "What You Can Build",
      "position": { "x": 1000, "y": -180 },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 560,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## What You Can Build\n\n*The graph has no ceiling.*\n\nüó∫Ô∏è **Thinking & Planning**\nRoadmaps, mind maps, knowledge bases, research notes, decision trees\n\nüìä **Dashboards**\nLive data nodes pulling from APIs, databases, spreadsheets ‚Äî updated in real time\n\n‚ö° **Automation**\nEvent nodes, trigger nodes, action nodes. Build Zapier-style workflows visually.\n\nü§ñ **AI Agents**\nPrompt nodes, model nodes, memory nodes. Wire up multi-step reasoning.\n\nüì± **Interactive Docs**\nForms, calculators, configurators. The graph responds to user input.\n\nüéÆ **Games & Simulations**\nState machines, behavior trees, game logic. Nodes are game objects.\n\nüîå **Integrations**\nAny API becomes a node. Any webhook becomes a trigger. **The graph talks to everything.**\n\n---\n\n*Today it's notes and roadmaps. Tomorrow it's anything you can imagine.*"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-problem",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "The Problem",
      "position": { "x": -200, "y": 0 },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## The Problem\n\nVisual thinking tools are **broken**:\n\n‚ùå **Graphs are ephemeral** ‚Äî screenshots, not files\n\n‚ùå **No stable identity** ‚Äî can't diff, can't version, can't review\n\n‚ùå **AI can't help** ‚Äî tools don't have machine-readable formats\n\n‚ùå **Build from scratch every time** ‚Äî no reuse, no templates, no remix\n\n‚ùå **Vendor lock-in** ‚Äî your thinking is trapped in someone else's app\n\n---\n\n**The deeper issue:** The graph isn't treated as the *real thing*. It's treated as a picture of the real thing."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-solution",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "The Solution",
      "position": { "x": 400, "y": 0 },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## The Solution\n\nMake the graph a **first-class artifact**:\n\n‚úÖ **Portable `.node` files** ‚Äî JSON you can store anywhere\n\n‚úÖ **Stable IDs** ‚Äî nodes and edges have identity across time\n\n‚úÖ **AI mutation contract** ‚Äî deltas, not rewrites; validation, not chaos\n\n‚úÖ **Web distribution** ‚Äî URLs, embeds, GitHub, templates\n\n‚úÖ **Progressive complexity** ‚Äî start with notes, evolve to workflows, end with execution\n\n---\n\n**The result:** A graph that survives time, tools, and assistants. Your thinking becomes infrastructure."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-alternatives",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Alternatives",
      "position": { "x": 1000, "y": 0 },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Why Not Existing Tools?\n\n| Tool | Limitation |\n|------|------------|\n| **Miro/FigJam** | Graphs are visual-only, no semantic structure |\n| **Notion** | Great for docs, weak for relationships |\n| **Obsidian** | File-based but graph is read-only |\n| **React Flow** | Developer tool, not end-user product |\n| **Lucidchart** | Proprietary, no AI integration |\n| **Excalidraw** | Drawing, not structured graphs |\n\n---\n\n**Twilite's difference:**\n- Graphs are *writable* by AI (not just viewable)\n- Graphs are *portable* (not locked in)\n- Graphs can *execute* (not just visualize)"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-artifact",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "The Artifact",
      "position": { "x": -200, "y": 420 },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 380,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## The Artifact\n\nA Twilite graph is a `.node` file:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"fileVersion\": \"1.0\",\n  \"metadata\": { ... },\n  \"settings\": { ... },\n  \"viewport\": { ... },\n  \"nodes\": [ ... ],\n  \"edges\": [ ... ],\n  \"groups\": [ ... ]\n}\n```\n\n**Properties:**\n- üìÅ Portable JSON (store in Git, S3, anywhere)\n- üîë Stable node/edge IDs (meaningful diffs)\n- üé® Settings + viewport (opens exactly as saved)\n- üîå Plugin extensions (namespaced custom data)\n- üìÑ Optional embedded document\n\n**Goal:** A graph that survives time, tools, and AI assistants."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-ai",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "AI Contract",
      "position": { "x": 400, "y": 420 },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 380,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## AI Contract\n\n**The key innovation:** A mutation protocol that lets AI safely edit graphs.\n\n### Actions\n```\ncreate   ‚Üí add nodes/edges\nupdate   ‚Üí modify existing by ID\ndelete   ‚Üí remove by ID\nbatch    ‚Üí multiple operations atomically\n```\n\n### Principles\n- **Deltas over rewrites** ‚Äî AI sends changes, not full snapshots\n- **Validation gates** ‚Äî malformed commands fail gracefully\n- **Minimal payloads** ‚Äî positions/handles optional; editor fills in\n- **Dry run mode** ‚Äî preview impact before applying\n\n### Outcome\nPaste JSON from ChatGPT/Claude ‚Üí graph appears instantly ‚Üí AI can evolve it coherently over time."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-workflow",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "The Workflow",
      "position": { "x": 1000, "y": 420 },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 380,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## The Workflow\n\n### For Humans\n1. **Describe** what you want to an AI\n2. **AI generates** graph JSON\n3. **Paste** into Twilite (Ctrl+V)\n4. **Graph appears** ‚Äî edit, extend, save\n\n### For AI Agents\n1. **Read** `.node` files from filesystem/URLs\n2. **Reason** about structure and relationships\n3. **Write** delta mutations (create/update/delete)\n4. **Validate** changes before applying\n\n### For Teams\n1. **Store** graphs in Git\n2. **Review** changes as diffs in PRs\n3. **Share** via URLs or embeds\n4. **Remix** templates and patterns"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-progression",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Progressive Complexity",
      "position": { "x": -200, "y": 860 },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Progressive Complexity\n\nNot every graph needs to execute. The platform supports a spectrum:\n\n### 1. Conceptual Graphs\n*Thinking, planning, knowledge*\n- Roadmaps, mind maps, research notes\n- Handles optional, edges are relationships\n\n### 2. Workflow Graphs\n*Typed connections, data flow*\n- Handles define inputs/outputs\n- Edges carry semantic meaning\n\n### 3. Executable Graphs\n*Scripts, plugins, live data*\n- Nodes run code (scripting API)\n- Background RPC for async operations\n- Plugin nodes extend capabilities"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-web",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Web Distribution",
      "position": { "x": 400, "y": 860 },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Web Distribution\n\nGraphs live on the web:\n\nüîó **Linkable**\n- Direct URLs to `.node` files\n- Query params: `?doc=https://...`\n- GitHub raw URLs work natively\n\nüì¶ **Shareable**\n- Export/import JSON\n- Embed in docs/wikis\n- Read-only viewer for publishing\n\nüé® **Remixable**\n- Template gallery\n- Fork and modify\n- Community patterns\n\n---\n\n**The format travels.** The editor is just the best way to interact with it."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-moat",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Defensibility",
      "position": { "x": 1000, "y": 860 },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## What Makes It Defensible\n\n*\"Better graph\" isn't the pitch. It's the mechanism.*\n\n### The Moat\n- **Artifact standardization** ‚Äî compatibility guarantees\n- **AI mutation contract** ‚Äî deltas, validation, safety\n- **Layout intelligence** ‚Äî small payloads, professional output\n- **Plugin contract** ‚Äî extensible without fragmentation\n- **Git-native workflows** ‚Äî diffs, PRs, history\n\n---\n\n**This is a governance + workflow moat**, not a model moat.\n\nCompetitors can copy features. They can't easily copy the contract that makes AI collaboration safe and predictable."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-wedges",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "First Wedges",
      "position": { "x": 100, "y": 1280 },
      "width": 700,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## First Wedges\n\n*Start with jobs that are true today:*\n\n### üó∫Ô∏è Roadmaps as Artifacts\nPlanning docs that can be versioned, reviewed, and evolved.\n\n### üìù AI-to-Graph Note Taking\n\"Turn this conversation into a diagram\" ‚Äî instant structure.\n\n### üîç PR-Reviewable Graphs\nChanges as deltas. Review graphs like you review code.\n\n### üß† Agent Domain Memory\nDurable state for long-running AI work. Graphs as context.\n\n---\n\n**Success metric:** A stranger can create a useful graph in 5 minutes and come back tomorrow to find it exactly as they left it."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-usecases",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Use Cases",
      "position": { "x": 860, "y": 1280 },
      "width": 700,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Use Cases\n\n| Category | Examples |\n|----------|----------|\n| **Visual Thinking** | Brainstorming, mind maps, ideation |\n| **Knowledge Graphs** | Concepts, relationships, hierarchies |\n| **Project Planning** | Roadmaps, timelines, dependencies |\n| **Learning** | Study diagrams, concept maps |\n| **Research** | Notes, citations, connections |\n| **Storytelling** | Narrative structures, character webs |\n| **Architecture** | System design, component maps |\n| **Decision Making** | Pros/cons, options, tradeoffs |\n\n---\n\n**Common thread:** Any time you need to *see* how things connect, Twilite can help ‚Äî and AI can help you build it."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tpt-next",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Next Steps",
      "position": { "x": 100, "y": 1700 },
